    <!-- Claiming Procedures Section -->
    <div class="row mb-4">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card border-warning">
                <div class="card-header bg-warning text-dark">
                    <h3 class="mb-0">The procedure for claiming the amount is as under </h3>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>
                        <strong>(a) Officers.</strong>
                        A copy of revised maturity benefits claim form <a href="../_forms/Appendix_G_Revised.pdf" target="_blank">Appendix G to AO 23/2002/AGI</a>
                        alongwith two photographs of first nominee for Extended Insurance are required to be forwarded to Army Group Insurance Directorate as advance
                        copy and two copies of revised Appendix G be forwarded to Controller of Defence Accounts (Officers) Pune four months in advance/ on receipt of
                        premature retirement orders/ or death of the Officer. SOS Part II Order in case of premature retirement
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>(b) JCOs & OR Retiring through Regiment/Corps Centre.</strong> Three copies
                        of revised maturity benefits claim form <a href="../_forms/Appendix_G_Revised.pdf" target="_blank">Appendix G to AO 23/2002/AGI</a> will be completed
                        by the unit, signed by the individual and countersigned by the OC unit for correctness of details and forwarded to the respective Record Office.
                        Senior Record Officer will scrutinise the claims for correctness and forward these claims to AGIF after getting the Part II portion thereof duly
                        completed by Accounts Officer (Not AAO) of the PAO (OR) as amended. Claims of individuals proceeding on discharge through Depot due to
                        causes other than normal retirement and in whose case Appx 'G' could not be initiated by unit will completed by OC Depot/Centre likewise and forwarded
                        to AGIF through the Record Officer for onward submission to AGIF.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>(c) JCOs & OR Retiring direct from Units/Hospitals.</strong> Claims of individuals proceeding to home direct from the
                        unit/hospitals, will be completed by the Unit/Hospitals as the case may be and forwarded to respective Record Offices for further action.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>(d) Recruits Discharged from the Centre.</strong> Claims in respect of recruits not found suitable and discharged from
                        service will be completed before they proceed on discharge. The claim will be signed by the individual, countersigned by the OC Unit and
                        forwarded to Record Offices for scrutiny and verification of deduction on account of AGIF recoveries. Record Offices will then forward the claim
                        to AGIF duly supported with copy of the final settlement Account.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>(e) Deserters.</strong> Deserters dismissed after three years should approach their Record Offices for
                        submission of AGIF Claim, which will be paid direct to the claimants. In case of deserter dismissed but not traceable,
                        their maturity benefits will be paid as per nomination, subject to the beneficiary executing a bound with two sureties.
                        However, if the amount is less than ₹ 1000/- payment may be made without executing an indemnity bond.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong>(f)</strong> Where deserters cannot be dismissed after three years due to desertion with arms or similar
                        circumstances of serious nature and are not apprehended after three years, they will be dismissed from the service
                        under Army Act Section 19 read with Army Rule 14 or Army Act Section 20 read with Army Rule 17 as the case may be
                        after ten years. Maturity benefits will be paid to nominee as per procedure outlined in Sub-Para (e) above after
                        the dismissal from service.
                    </p>
                </div>
